<paragraph id="D87CAF32E04BBC73FE94F688F06D5F88" blockId="6.[171,1570,401,1471]" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">
Previously recorded material: 
<bibRefCitation id="BC52D2C3E04BBC73FCF1F689F1785ED1" author="Ricardo" box="[806,1040,1229,1264]" firstAuthor="Ricardo" journalOrPublisher="Annals and magazine of natural history" pageId="6" pageNumber="289" pagination="234 - 282" part="15" refId="ref11256" refString="RICARDO, G. 1925. New species of Asilidae from South Africa. Annals and magazine ofnatuml history 15 (9): 234 - 282." title="New species of Asilidae from South Africa" type="journal article" year="1925">Ricardo (1925)</bibRefCitation>
did not designate a holotype but merely dealt with her specimens as syntypes. I hereby designate one of the males in the BMNH as lectotype and the other ♂ and 
<specimenCount id="CEC564BBE04BBC73FCB6F759F1035F7A" box="[865,1131,1309,1348]" pageId="6" pageNumber="289" type="generic">♀ paralectotypes</specimenCount>
. Ricardo also records 2 
<emphasis id="EAB77320E04BBC73FA28F75AF3785F05" box="[1535,1552,1310,1339]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">♀</emphasis>
, from Kimberley and from Cape Colony. These specimens are not in the BMNH but probably in the South African Museum (Cape Town). 
<bibRefCitation id="BC52D2C3E04BBC73FBC8F736F0425FAB" author="Oldroyd's" box="[1055,1322,1394,1430]" firstAuthor="Oldroyd's" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Natal Museum" pageId="6" pageNumber="289" pagination="1 - 171" part="22" refId="ref11155" refString="e 1974. An introduction to the robber flies (Diptera: Asilidae) of southern Africa. Annals ofthe Natal Museum 22: 1 - 171." title="An introduction to the robber flies (Diptera: Asilidae) of southern Africa" type="journal article" year="1974">Oldroyd’s (1974)</bibRefCitation>
types of salicior included a ♀ from Twee Rivieren which deﬁnitely belongs to 
<emphasis id="EAB77320E04BBC73FBA9F7D8F1F15F88" box="[1150,1177,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="289">D</emphasis>
. hirtus.
</paragraph>
